        "title": "13.3 in (Lightweight/Ultra Portable) Laptop Help",
        "published": 1284264780,
        "updated": 1284264780,
        "related": [{
            "href": "http://forums.g4tv.com/showthread.php?t\u003d157063\u0026goto\u003dnewpost"
        }],
        "alternate": [{
            "href": "http://forums.g4tv.com/showthread.php?t\u003d157063",
            "type": "text/html"
        }],
        "content": {
            "direction": "ltr",
            "content": "\u003cdiv\u003ehey everyone...\u003cbr\u003e\nWell I am in need of a new laptop for school.  Won't be doing any gaming on it - mostly for reading e-textbooks and a bit of word processing.  Portability is VERY VERY important to me and I want something under 4.4 lbs (less the better!).  I am also thinking of being able to get 1080P movies and watching them on my 52 inch panasonic TV via HDMI (If not though this is not my priority - once again this is for school but this would be a cool feature to have available). So far, I am looking at this \u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n1) \u003ca href\u003d\"http://www.newegg.ca/Product/Product.aspx?Item\u003dN82E16834146800\"\u003ehttp://www.newegg.ca/Product/Product...82E16834146800\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(No HDMI) but powerful processor (for my price range) and it claims to have 5.5 hours of battery life.  Its cpu has 1660 on 3dmark2006 cpu. A bit heavy but not too bad.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n2) \u003ca href\u003d\"http://www.tigerdirect.ca/applications/SearchTools/item-details.asp?EdpNo\u003d6594317\u0026amp;\"\u003ehttp://www.tigerdirect.ca/applicatio...EdpNo\u003d6594317\u0026amp;\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\ncsid\u003dITD\u0026amp;body\u003dMAIN#detailspecs\u003cbr\u003e\n(Has HDMI) Weak processor on benchmarks it only gets 1167 on 3dmark2006 cpu.  Not sure on the battery life\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n3) \u003ca href\u003d\"http://www.tigerdirect.ca/applications/SearchTools/item-details.asp?EdpNo\u003d6488405\u0026amp;CatId\u003d2508\"\u003ehttp://www.tigerdirect.ca/applicatio...405\u0026amp;CatId\u003d2508\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Has HDMI) but a VERY weak processor (3dmark - 649).  Apparently 8 hrs of battery life.   \u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\nWhats your opinion on these.  Im leaning more towards the lenovo but the HDMI is kind of cool feature for the toshiba...\u003cbr\u003e\nif you guys have anything like the lenovo - with hdmi maybe Id be ecstatic.  If not I think thats the route im going to go.  Let me know what you think.\u003c/div\u003e"
        },
